                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d317">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">884.001 Selassie I/370: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the
                        Emperor of Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Haile Selassie I</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-20">May 20,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have received Your Majesty’s message informing me of your return to Addis
                    Ababa, and I assure you of the satisfaction with which I have received these
                    tidings. On behalf of the people and Government of the United States I have
                    great pleasure in extending to Your Majesty my most sincere felicitations on
                    this notable occasion and my best wishes for Your Majesty’s health and
                    happiness.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Franklin</hi> D. <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
